The Vertical Digger has two modes: "Mining Everything" and "Only Mining Ores".

It will dig straight down until it hits Bedrock.

Per default, the Vertical Digger has a radius of 2 blocks, meaning it mines in a 5x5 area.

Placing a Phantom Booster on top of it will double the radius.
Up to 3 Phantom Boosters can be stacked above the digger, allowing a maximum radius of 16 (or 33x33).

Crystallized Canola Seeds:
To get even better oil, place the fermented oil on the ground and throw in a crystallized canola seed to get crystallized canola.

To get started with embers, you need this hammer.

It is used to craft plates.

However you can also use the hammer from immersive engineering.

For getting ember(energy) you need ember crystals.

To get them you have to place the ember bore on bedrock and pipe coal into it.
Then you can extract ember crystals and ember shards.
For item storage there are these bins.
For fluid storage you can use this.
For item transportation you need the pipes and an item extractor.
The item extractor has to be placed on the inventory you want to draw items out of and has to be powered with a redstone signal.
For fluid transportation you need the pipes and a fluid extractor.
The fluid extractor has to be placed on the tank you want to draw liquids out of and has to be powered with a redstone signal.

To transfer ember(energy) you have to use the Ember Emitter and Receptor.

The Emitter needs a redstone signal.

To connect them grab your Tinker's Hammer and Shift+Rightclick on the Receptor and then normal Rightclick on the Emitter.
